Name: Description
Asthma Hospitalizations:
Number of asthma hospitalizations among NYC resident children by age groups (0 to 4, 5 to 17 and 0 to 17).
Rate of asthma hospitalizations per 10,000 children in specific age groups (0 to 4, 5 to 17 and 0 to 17).

Name: Source Notes
Asthma Hospitalizations: New York State Statewide Planning and Research Cooperative System (SPARCS) Deidentified Hospital Discharge Data, retrieved from New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene NYC Tracking Program: Environment and Health Data Portal. [Asthma Hospitalizations; 2000-2016]. http://a816-dohbesp.nyc.gov/IndicatorPublic/

Name: Notes
Asthma Hospitalizations:
Rates are calculated by using number of asthma hospitalizations among NYC resident children for particular age group, divided by the population of children for the same age group, expressed as cases per 10,000 resident children for the respective age group (i.e. asthma hospitalization among NYC resident children ages 0 to 4, divided by the population of children ages 0 to 4, expressed as cases per 10,000 population ages 0 to 4).

UHFs with the value of 0 represent data suppressed by DOHMH due to small sample size or insufficient data.
